{"key":"processedPost-11938637","value":{"id":11938637,"first":11937646,"last":11938637,"when":1265000044,"utime":"02/01/10 06:54 AM","content":"Mushrooms are very high in calcium, so it really helps to have plenty of it in your substrates.&nbsp; The best way to get it is with gypsum, since it will not raise your pH.&nbsp; Mushrooms prefer a slightly acidic substrate, so adding a small amount of spent coffee grounds before pasteurization of nearly any substrate will help.<br /><br />It's not that neglecting gypsum will result in failure, it's more a case of fine-tuning for best performance.<br />RR","title":"Re: Monotub additives: coffee, gypsum? Thoughts?"}}